  %h1 Privacy Policy
  %p Last Updated: July 7, 2011  %p Qwiqq Privacy Policy  %p Qwiqq, Inc. (“We”, “Us,” “Our,” or “Qwiqq”) provides you with this Privacy Policy to inform you of the collection and use policies and practices that apply to information collected on our website at Qwiqq.com and our mobile applications available for via download from the Web Site or from another source (our “Service”). We are committed to giving you transparency of our privacy practices and control over your data in connection with Qwiqq's Service. “You” or “Your” means the person, company or other legal entity which is accepting this Privacy Policy.  %p This Privacy Policy covers Qwiqq's treatment of personally identifiable information ("Personal Information") and other data that Qwiqq gathers when you are accessing Qwiqq's Service. If you do not accept this Privacy Policy or you do not meet or comply with these provisions, you may not use the Service. The Service is not available to individuals who are younger than 13 years old.  
  %h1 Your Personal Information
  %p 
    %b Personal Information You Provide to Us: 
    We may receive and store any information you enter on our Service or provide to us in any other way. In order to register for and use the Services, you must provide certain Personal Information. The types of Personal Information collected may include your name, email address, Twitter usernames and Facebook usernames. We also automatically receive your location when you use the Service. The Personal Information you provide is used for such purposes as allowing you to set up a user account and profile that can be used to interact with other users through the Service, improving the content of the Service, customizing the advertising and content you see, and communicating with you about specials and new features. We may also draw upon this Personal Information in order to adapt the Services to your needs, to research the effectiveness of our network and Services, and to develop new tools for the Service.
  %p     %b Your Responsibilities: 
    You are responsible for maintaining the accuracy, confidentiality and security of your Personal Information reflected in your account. You can review and edit your Personal Information by logging in to your account and adjusting your settings.
  %p 
    %b Information Collected Automatically: 
    When you use the Service, Qwiqq automatically receives and records information on our server logs from your browser or mobile platform, including your location, IP address, cookie information, and the page you requested. We do not treat this data as Personal Information, except where we are required to do otherwise under applicable law. Qwiqq only shares this data with third parties in aggregate and unidentified form. We may provide aggregate information to our partners about how our customers, collectively, use our site and applications, so that our partners may also understand how often people use their services and our Service.
  %p 
    %b Email Communications: 
    If you do not want to receive commercial email or other mail from us, please indicate your preference during the registration process or by making a modification on your account settings page or through the 'settings' tab on our Web Site once you're logged into the Service. Please note that if you do not want to receive legal notices from us, such as notices regarding this Privacy Policy, those legal notices will still govern your use of the Service, and you are responsible for reviewing such legal notices for changes. We may receive a confirmation when you open an email from Qwiqq if your computer supports this type of program. Qwiqq uses this confirmation to help us make emails more interesting and helpful and improve our Service.
    
  %h1 Sharing of Your Personal Information within the Qwiqq Community  %p Personal Information about our users is an integral part of our business. We neither rent nor sell your Personal Information to anyone. Qwiqq may share your Personal Information only as described below.  %p
    %b Friends: 
    Your "friends" can see the location and time of each of your posts and your Personal Information, including your first name and last name, email, photo, hometown, and links to your Twitter and Facebook accounts (if you have connected those accounts to your Qwiqq account). Friends reading this information may use it or disclose it to other individuals or entities without our control and without your knowledge. We therefore urge you to think carefully about including any specific information you may deem private in your written comments or posts. We are not responsible for Personal Information that you voluntarily choose to display or exchange with others using the Service.  We are not responsible for information that you may elect to exchange outside of the Service.
  %p 
    %b Information Shared with Everyone: 
    One of the primary reasons people use Qwiqq is to share content with others. Non-personal information such as your username and photo, your hometown, a list of your friends, and the comments you write is shared by default with the entire Qwiqq community. You expressly agree that other users exclusively own all right, title and interest in and to all of their Personal Information and that you will not sell, share, distribute, publish, advertise or reference their Personal Information except as provided in this Privacy Policy.
  %p 
    %b Adding Your Home Address As A Venue: 
    You should be aware that if you or your friends post a deal from your home as a venue, that information will be available to others and may be published by third parties not under our control. To remove a post you published from the Service (including your home address), tap the delete button that appears beside the post.
    
